<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net" agent="Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/136.0.0.0 Safari/537.36" version="27.0.9" pages="8">
  <diagram name="Page-1" id="F0_yebCazgMxKxPeHt2I">
    <mxGraphModel grid="1" page="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="dF_YD_F9VKaIOS6fXDXN-1" value="&lt;h1&gt;1. The Key Concept&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;As per the Requirement:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. Users and Universities will have its own blockchain wallet to send transactions over the blockchain network.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. There will be permission control management system for the Universities.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. The universities should have the ability to generate unique QR codes for the certificates uploaded into the network.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;a. Certificate upload will happen in Bulk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;b. Each certificate&#39;s PDF data will be uploaded into the network.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;c. On successful uploading of the certificate data, it should create an unique and blockchain secured QR code linked with the certificate data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;d. The certificates will be linked to University Wallet and User wallet.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. API should be available to integrate with the University System.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. QR Codes will open a portal where the everything that is stored in the blockchain will be shown about that certificate.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="10" y="200" width="430" height="370" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="dF_YD_F9VKaIOS6fXDXN-3" value="&lt;h1&gt;2. Solution (Full dApp)&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. We can have two saperate dApp which will be connected to MetaMask wallet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;a. Certificate Explorer (Public User Interface)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;b. Enterprise Panel (For Universities)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Certificate explorer will be used by the users to view their certificate information and etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. Enterprise Panel will be for the Universities when they will initiate the process of the QR Code generation for the certificates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. The smart contracts will have proper RBAC mechanism to handle the administration of certificate metadata.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. We can use Private Etherium Network to store the certificate metadata and IPFS private network to store the PDFs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="470" y="200" width="340" height="370" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
